-- Climex Exchange Handles 50,000 Voluntary CO2 Offsets in Auction
-- B y   A l e s s a n d r o   V i t e l l i
-- 2012-09-21T16:51:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-21/climex-exchange-handles-50-000-voluntary-co2-offsets-in-auction.html
Climex BV, a carbon permit and
offset exchange in Amsterdam, bought 50,000 Verified Emission
Reductions on behalf of an unidentified Dutch company in a
reverse auction at 3.77 euros ($4.90) each, the bourse said.  The exchange bought Gold Standard voluntary offsets from
renewable energy projects, it said in an e-mailed statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
